Since $\angle ABD = \angle CBD = 90^\circ$, quadrilateral $ABCD$ is cyclic.  Therefore, $\angle CED = \angle CAD = \boxed{47^\circ}$.

Since $\angle BAE$ is an inscribed angle which intercepts diameter $AB,$ we have $\angle BAE = 90^\circ.$  Therefore, $\angle AEB = 90^\circ - 43^\circ = 47^\circ.$

