Let $x = \angle CEB.$  Then $\angle CBE = 90^\circ - x,$ so
\[\angle ACD = \angle ACB + \angle BCD = (90^\circ - x) + 90^\circ = 180^\circ - x.\]Also, $\angle AED = \angle AEB + \angle BEC + \angle CED = 47^\circ + (90^\circ - x) + \angle CED.$  But $\angle AED = \angle ACD,$ so
\[180^\circ - x = 47^\circ + (90^\circ - x) + \angle CED.\]Solving for $\angle CED,$ we find $\angle CED = \boxed{43^\circ}.$

Since $\overline{AB}$ is a diameter, $\angle AEB = 90^\circ$.  Also, $\angle ABE = 180^\circ - \angle BAE - \angle EAB = 180^\circ - 43^\circ - 90^\circ = 47^\circ$, so $\angle CEB = \angle ABE = 47^\circ$.

Since $BC$ and $BD$ are tangent to the circle, $\angle BCD = \angle BDC = 90^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle CED = \angle CEB + \angle BED = 47^\circ + \angle BAD$.

