Since $AB$ is a diameter, $\angle ABD = 90^\circ$, so $\angle BAD = \angle BAE - \angle EAD = 43^\circ - \angle BED$.  Therefore,
\[\angle CED = 47^\circ + \angle BAD = 47^\circ + 43^\circ - \angle BED = \boxed{90^\circ}.\]

Since $\angle BAE = 43^\circ,$ $\angle BEO = 2 \cdot \angle BAE = 86^\circ.$

