A = (-2,0);
B = (1,4);
C = (-3,2);
Cp = (3,2);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(C--Cp);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, N);
label("$C$", C, W);
label("$C'$", Cp, E);
[/asy]

Then $CC'$ is a horizontal segment of length $|3 - (-3)| = \boxed{6}.$

Solution:
Reflecting a point over the $y$-axis negates its $x$-coordinate.  Thus, $C' = (3, 2).$

