Then $\angle APT = \angle BPT = 90^\circ,$ so $ABPT$ is cyclic.  Then $\angle AOB = 2 \angle ATB,$ where $\angle ATB$ is the external angle of $\triangle TBS.$

Since $PA$ is tangent to the circle, $\angle PAB = \angle PBA.$  Since $PR$ and $PS$ are tangent to the circle,
\[\angle RPS = \angle SPR = \angle PAB.\]Then $\angle APS = 180^\circ - \angle RPS = 180^\circ - \angle SPR = \angle APB = 40^\circ.$

