Then $\angle STB = 180^\circ - \angle ATS = 140^\circ.$  Also, $\angle SBT = \angle RBP = \angle PAB = \angle PBA,$ so $\triangle SBT$ is isosceles.  Hence, $\angle TBS = \angle STB/2 = \boxed{70^\circ}.$

