Let $x = \angle AOB.$  Then $\angle AOT = \angle BOT = \frac{180^\circ - x}{2}.$  Also, $\angle APT = \angle BPT = 90^\circ,$ so $\angle APB = 180^\circ - \angle APT - \angle BPT = \frac{x}{2}.$

Then $\angle APB + \angle AOT + \angle BOT = \frac{x}{2} + \frac{180^\circ - x}{2} + \frac{180^\circ - x}{2} = 180^\circ - \angle AOB.$  Since $\angle APB = 40^\circ,$
\[140^\circ - \angle AOB = 180^\circ - \angle AOB.\]This gives us $\angle AOB = \boxed{40^\circ}.$

